==English==
===Pronunciation===
dĭsk, /dɪsk/, /<tt>dIsk</tt>/

===Noun===
'''disk''' ([[disks]])
#A [[thin]], [[flat]], [[circular]] [[plate]] or similar [[object]]
#* A coin is a '''disk''' of metal
#Something [[resembling]] a disk
#* The Moon's '''disk''' cut off light from the Sun
#A [[vinyl]] [[phonograph]] / [[gramophone]] [[record]]
#* Turn the '''disk''' over, it has finished

====Computing Usage====
In International English, ''disk'' is the correct spelling for magnetic ''disks''. If the medium is optical, the variant [[disc]] is used.

#Magnetic medium
#*Hodge still uses '''[[floppy disk]] s''' from the 80's
#Optical medium
#*Gazza bought some blank '''[[compact disc]] s''' yesterday

US spelling dictates that '''[[disc]]''' should be used for all mediums of data storing disks/discs.

